CVID, Common Variable Immunodeficiency Disorder: This immunodeficiency disorder can cause recurrent infections, low levels of immunoglobulins, and other health problems. It is a primary immunodeficiency disorder, meaning that it is not caused by another medical condition.

Hyperimmunoglobulin E syndrome (HIES): This rare disorder is characterized by eczema, recurrent infections, and high levels of IgE. It is caused by a mutation in the STAT3 gene, which is involved in the immune system.
Selective IgA deficiency: This is the most common type of antibody deficiency. It does not usually cause any symptoms, but people with this condition may be more susceptible to infections.
Transient hypogammaglobulinemia of infancy: This is a temporary condition that occurs in some infants. It usually resolves on its own, but some infants may need treatment.
X-linked agammaglobulinemia (XLA): This is a rare genetic disorder that affects males. It causes low levels of all types of immunoglobulins and can lead to severe infections.
Eczema: This is a common skin condition that causes dry, itchy, and inflamed skin. It can be caused by a variety of factors, including allergies, irritants, and stress.
Seborrheic dermatitis: This is a common skin condition that causes red, scaly patches on the scalp, face, and chest. It is caused by an overgrowth of a yeast-like fungus called Malassezia.
Rosacea: This is a chronic skin condition that causes redness, flushing, and pimples on the face. It is caused by a combination of genetic and environmental factors.
Scleroderma: This is a rare autoimmune disease that causes the skin and connective tissues to thicken and harden. It can also affect the internal organs.
Polymyositis: This is an autoimmune disease that causes inflammation of the muscles. It can cause muscle weakness, pain, and fatigue.
Hypersensitivity reactions: These are reactions to substances that are normally harmless. They can range from mild to severe, and can include anaphylaxis.
Blepharospasm: This is a condition that causes the eyelids to blink uncontrollably. It can be caused by a variety of factors, including stress, fatigue, and certain medications.
Hemorrhoids: These are swollen veins in the anus or rectum. They can cause pain, itching, and bleeding.

Depression: This is a common mental health disorder that causes feelings of sadness, loss of interest, and fatigue. It can be caused by a variety of factors, including genetics, life events, and medical conditions.
